Just below there is
 if (ignoreTypeArgs) {
      return true;
    }
Why is no test needed for the raw component?  What if this method were called with two arguments:  raw Class and raw List?  I suspect that subtype and supertype must have some specific relationship, such as that their raw types are the same or in some subtyping relationship.  Could you document that?

Below there is also
    if (subtypeTypeArgs.isEmpty()) {
      return true;
    }
How can that happen?

