This test looks wrong to me.  I think the && should be ||.
However, I would rewrite it to correspond closely to the Javadoc comment @code type} and {@code typeMirror} must both be declared types.:
        if (!(type.getKind() == TypeKind.DECLARED && typeMirror.getKind() == TypeKind.DECLARED)) {
            return false;
	}
I think a closer correspondence between the Javadoc and the code makes the code easier to understand.

